title: mojo.core.CodeModule
description:
Carries information about code modules that are loaded into a process.
See src/google_breakpad/processor/code_module.h

baseAddress.title: mojo.core.Int64
baseAddress.description: The base address of this code module as it was loaded by the process.

codeFile.title: mojo.core.String
codeFile.description: The path or file name that the code module was loaded from.

codeIdentifier.title: mojo.core.String
codeIdentifier.description:
An identifying string used to discriminate between multiple versions and
builds of the same code module.  This may contain a uuid, timestamp,
version number, or any combination of this or other information, in an
implementation-defined format.

debugFile.title: mojo.core.String
debugFile.description:
The filename containing debugging information associated with the code
module.  If debugging information is stored in a file separate from the
code module itself (as is the case when .pdb or .dSYM files are used),
this will be different from code_file.  If debugging information is
stored in the code module itself (possibly prior to stripping), this
will be the same as code_file.

debugIdentifier.title: mojo.core.String
debugIdentifier.description:
An identifying string similar to code_identifier, but identifies a
specific version and build of the associated debug file.  This may be
the same as code_identifier when the debug_file and code_file are
identical or when the same identifier is used to identify distinct
debug and code files.

size.title: mojo.core.Int64
size.description: The size of the code module.

version.title: mojo.core.String
version.description: A human-readable representation of the code module's version.
